Bahati's baby Mama Yvette Obura has opened up on a lot of issues surrounding her relationship with Bahati and Diana Marua. In a Q and A session with her fans on Instagram, the mother of one admitted she was paid for her epic appearance on Bahati's reality show. Yvette also praised Diana and said she was a great woman both on and off camera. “True, I’m on good terms with Diana Marua. I’d say a lot, but I thank God for where we are right now.” Yvette admitted her baby daddy comes through financially and always pays for trips when their daughter Mueni travels. However, she denied having private meetings with Bahati or a tattoo of the singer’s name on her body. “I never look at Diana Marua’s life and wish I were in that position,” she said.